title: Grateful Dead Live at McNichols Sports Arena on 1994-12-01
description:
Set 1

Hell In A Bucket, Sugaree, Wang Dang Doodle, Loser, If The Shoe Fits, When I Paint My Masterpiece*, Bird Song

Set 2

Here Comes Sunshine, Saint Of Circumstance, Way to Go Home, Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Space-> All Along The Watchtower-> The Days Between-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Brokedown Palace

* Weir on acoustic guitar

reviews.review_text:
Thirty-First Days Between 31/41: Eyes (14:31) -> Drumz (30:13) -> Watchtower (7:55) -> Days Between (14:16) -> Throwing Stones -> NFA. 

Absolutely love this groove in Sugaree... Wailing Garcia. Just skip the Shoe Fits. I imagine it fits. Good Bird Song. Decent Eyes -> tripped out Drumz, a definite high point of a late-90s show, without question. Psychedelically delightful, it segues into Watchtower then Days Between. 

Brokedown Palace stumbles, then encores, and is beautiful as ever. Nice Kesey story re: Brokedown Palace and the place and meaning of art: http://artsites.ucsc.edu/gdead/agdl/brok.html.
